****Dorset-based male actor needed (paid)****

**Playing age:** 55‚Äì75

**Date:** Saturday 20th December 2025

**Company:** Earth Kin Events (earthkinevents.co.uk)

**Event:** Earth Kin Events** Winter Solstice celebration**. A live celebration with singing, drumming, poetry, storytelling and more to celebrate the Winter Solstice. 

**Location:** The Earth House, Ancient Technology Centre,  Cranborne, nr. Wimborne, Dorset 

**What we need: **We‚Äôre looking for a confident, grounded performer with an **excellent head for lines** and a touch of **‚Äúwizard energy‚Äù** ‚Äî by which we mean:
* Warm, wise, magical presence
* Gravitas, slight edge, storyteller vibes
* (Feel free to show your interpretation!)
* Performer required to perform 8 minute 'story poem' during the first half

**Timings: **First half will be 7.30pm - 8.30pm . . . you are welcome to come into the celebrations to perform this bit only and leave directly afterwards, or you are very welcome to stay and enjoy all the celebrations with a plus one. The celebrations will last from 7.30- 10.30pm, site bar and craft stalls will open at 6pm. All artists provided with hot food and drinks.

**Costume: **Provided 

**Fee: **¬£150 

**What's next:** I‚Äôll be on Zoom this Wednesday 26th Nov in the evening for meet and greets, would love to hear you sight read the poem (I will send in advance) and we can have a brief chat about any questions you might have.  

If you‚Äôre interested, please email me on earthkinevents@gmail.com so we can arrange a time. . . (email is best as social media messages can be so hard to keep track of!)  

Thanks so much for reading, 

Ellie 

(Pic for algorithm tax - credit, Pixabay)

# Estate of Suspicion
## Mystery Game for Dickens on the Strand

Paid: $125 

Non-union

Location: Galveston, TX

Dec 6th & 7th (Day-time)

Rehearsal: Dec 2nd & 3rd evenings in Houston (virtual possible)

## Submission Link

[[https://forms.gle/1f3AhSdaMDFZputF6](https://forms.gle/1f3AhSdaMDFZputF6)](https://forms.gle/1f3AhSdaMDFZputF6)

We are looking for FIVE performers for our mystery game at Dickens on the Strand. This call is for two days and the pay is $125, and your festival admission. You will be responsible for your own lodging, transportation. Please read the rest of the details below.

## About the Game

This game is currently still in development but it will be interactive. Players must interview each character as a suspect to a mystery. To win the game, the player must assemble the clues and accuse one of the suspects. Winners will take home a prize provided by the festival.

## Important Details for the Event
* **Acting Skills: **Improvisation is key! Actors are asked to stay in character while out on festival grounds. You will only need to memorize one page of character information.
* **Outdoor Setting**: The event will be held mostly outdoors, so please prepare accordingly for the weather.
* **Costumes and Props**: XP Hou will provide necessary items for the production. You may be asked to provide shoes. Personal items may be worn at the discretion of the director.
* **Mobility**: Be ready for significant standing, walking, and engaging in conversations with players throughout the event.
* **Crowd Presence**: Expect a lively, festive crowd. A comfort level with interacting in large, bustling settings will be essential.

## Characters

All genders and ages are encouraged to submit.
* Ms. Marie Greggor - Housekeeper (60s - 70s)
* Mr. David Carton - Lawyer (50s - 60s)
* Benedict Waverly - Longshoreman (25yr - 35yr)
* Lady Carla Carrington - Widow sister (50s - 70s)
* Pamela Prigg - Nurse (20s - 40s)
## Synopsis

Winston Prescott, a Galveston shipping magnate, built an empire before retreating from the world after losing his wife and daughter. Now he‚Äôs dead under suspicious circumstances. His estranged sister, Carla Carrington, returns for the will reading led by family lawyer David Carton. Also present are housekeeper Marie Greggor, nurse Pamela Prigg, and Greggor‚Äôs unexpected guest, Benedict Waverly.

The will delivers two shocks: the entire Prescott Estate goes to Nurse Prigg unless a legitimate heir appears, and a coroner‚Äôs letter suggests Winston‚Äôs death may be murder. The sheriff halts the inheritance and declares all present suspects. Mr. Carton becomes acting executor as the investigation begins.

Then Greggor reveals her guest‚Äôs true identity ‚Äî Benedict is the secret son of Winston, making him the presumed heir. Carla immediately contests, and Pamela refuses to yield. Tensions erupt, and players must comb Galveston‚Äôs Strand District to uncover the truth.

items.text:
Casting Call!

We have one role left to cast!!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own.

Looking to cast supporting character John Marlow.

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

**Jigsaw Casting is seeking a Weather Reporter for a Quick Serve Restaurant Campaign across Canada**

We are also open to a host or news reporter. They‚Äôre likeable, relatable, charming, and capable of giving an authentic performance. The ideal candidate has real-life reporting experience. The age range is 40s. Someone that knows the weather like the back of their hand, the subtlety and nuances. They‚Äôre confident and engaging, with a comedic sensibility.

This will be filming in Toronto. If someone lives far from this area, travel and accommodation will be provided.

**IF YOU KNOW OF SOMEONE, PLEASE PASS THIS ON!**

This is a non union job. Compensation if selected: $3,075.00. Buyout is based on survival of the edit and includes all lifts, edits, versions.

Must be available for these Important dates:

Recall: Wed Nov 26th, 2025 in Toronto Studio or via zoom if you live far away from Toronto.

Wardrobe: Dec 5th, 2025.

Shoot Date: Dec 9th with a weather hold of Dec 10th, 2025.

*Talent will be shooting outside, in Toronto.

items.text:
‚Ä¢CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM 
Project Title: The Weight of Yesterday 
Production Type: Independent Feature Film
Shoot Dates: December 5th - 7th
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $500/day + Reel + IMDb Credit

SYNOPSIS:
A week before their high school‚Äôs final closure, five classmates reunite to bury a time capsule they created years ago. What begins as a nostalgic farewell quickly spirals into a raw confrontation of the truths, betrayals, and dreams that shaped their youth and the adulthood that awaits.
NOW CASTING ‚Äì LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES:

 LEAD ROLES:
Aiden (Male, 18‚Äì23)
Ambitious, witty, and fiercely protective. A natural leader haunted by a decision he made senior year that fractured the group.

Riley (Female, 18‚Äì24)
Intelligent and emotionally layered. She‚Äôs the planner of the reunion, but secretly fears what might resurface. Carries herself with quiet authority.

Lana (Female, 19‚Äì25)
Charming and impulsive with a magnetic presence. Struggles with stability and hides vulnerability behind a fearless exterior.

SUPPORTING ROLES:
Tessa (Female, 18‚Äì23)
Reserved, observant, and deeply reflective. Once the outsider of the group, she now holds crucial pieces of the past they all want to forget.

Ms. Grant (Female, 30s‚Äì40s)
A former teacher turned school counselor. Warm, insightful, and a mentor to many, but carries her own regrets about the group‚Äôs final year.

TO SUBMIT:
Email your headshot, resume, and city of residence to:
everlastfilming@gmail.com 

Subject line: ‚Äú[Your Name] ‚Äì Role Submission for The Weight of Yesterday ‚Äù

topComments.text:
This is a scam. How clueless can people be. 
Legit Feature films do not shoot in three days 
They do not engage in business with a generic Gmail account 
And they don't ask your city of residence

My name is Jerry Valentino Wright ‚Äî published author of 11 books and creator of multiple cinematic universes that are READY to be adapted to film.

I‚Äôm seeking one serious, visionary producer or small production company who sees potential where others see limits ‚Äî someone who wants to help bring a powerful, original franchise to life.

I have several finished books that are visually explosive, emotionally gripping, and built for the screen, including:

üé¨ The Eternal War: Light vs Darkness ‚Äî
A supernatural action-drama with apocalyptic tension, angelic warfare, moral conflict, and a lead character whose destiny shifts the balance between Heaven and Hell.

üé¨ Edge of the Block (series) ‚Äî
Urban, gritty, raw, perfect for a streaming series or limited-run Netflix-style drama.

üé¨ No Mercy Left, The Last Revelation, The Final Prophecy ‚Äî
End-times thrillers with cinematic visuals, spiritual depth, and blockbuster potential.

These aren‚Äôt ‚Äúideas.‚Äù
These are published works, already moving thousands of readers ‚Äî stories built with character arcs, emotional weight, and world-building filmmakers dream about.

I‚Äôm looking for the RIGHT partner:
üëâ A producer with vision
üëâ A director who loves building new worlds
üëâ An indie studio hungry for original IP
üëâ Someone who wants to turn books into films with real impact

If you‚Äôre interested in reading the logline, synopsis, or treatment ‚Äî or if you‚Äôre a filmmaker who loves collaborating with authors ‚Äî comment below or DM me directly.

Let‚Äôs build something legendary.
Let‚Äôs create a film people will feel, not just watch.

+++ Was erlauben" Constantin? +++
Eine Chronologie sozialer K√§lte

Auch die Mallorca Zeitung berichtet

Kinoproduktion "Der perfekte Urlaub" 

Okt. Nov. 
Auf Mallorca gesuchte Komparsen (√ºberwiegend intern. Touristen) bekommen  82.50 EUR Brutto pro Nachtdreh (bei 5 Drehtagen,10.11.-14.11) je 10 Std. Arbeit + 1Std.Pause
(Abrechnung n. Mindestlohn, Spanien)

6.Nov.
Constantin Film sucht (scheinbar aus der Not) nun auch  kurzfristig aus Deutschland Komparsen incl. √úbernachtungsm√∂glichkeit
 jedoch OHNE Gage, Nachtzulage und  Flugkostenerstattung f√ºr 5 Drehn√§chte
 (s. Online-Gesuch 
(Faire Gagen berichtete)

Nach massiver Kritik vieler Filmschaffender  und auch unser Initiative "Faire Gagen":
Umstrittenes Gesuch wird von Constantin Film kommentarlos gel√∂scht. 

08.Nov.
Constantin Film sucht wiederum in Deutschland Komparsen f√ºr brsagte 5 Drehn√§chte nun  MIT Flugkosten√ºbernahme und 50.00 EUR  Aufwandsentsch√§digung (Gage) diesmal via Agentur Producer's Friend.

"Faire Gagen" fordert dennoch respektvolle Gagen nach dem in Deutschland geltenden gesetzlichen Mindestlohn  einer Nachtzulage und eine  Gleichbehandlung  ALLER  Komparsen am Set via "Offenen Brief" 

"Mallorca Zeitung" (MZ) fragt daraufhin ebenfalls kritisch nach.

Antwort Constantin Film an MZ:  "Die aus Deutschland eingeflogenen Komparsen bekommen selbstverst√§ndlich den in Deutschland √ºblichen Mindestlohn mit Nachtzulage und  auch die Flugkosten-Erstattung (s. Beitrag aus der MZ)

19.Nov. 14.45h
Die Initiative "Faire Gagen" hat trotz Offenen Brief und nochmaliger Bitte, kein Statement und  damit auch keinerlei Erkl√§rung oder Entschuldigung f√ºr die vielen irritierten und ver√§rgerten Filmschaffenden  von Constantin Film erhalten.

Dazu die F√§lle der Vergangenheit bei ebenfalls gro√üen Kinoproduktionen mit den Versuchen bei  hunderten  Komparsen den deutschen Mindestlohn zu umgehen  den wir jedoch ebenfalls durchsetzen konnten.
(Faire Gagen berichtete)

Was bleibt ist ein respektloses Durcheinander mit immer wieder ver√§rgerten, verprellten und verwunderten Komparsen und der Frage: 

"Warum Constantin Film  gerade im eh schon schlecht bezahlten Filmgewerk Komparserie und  Kleindarstellerei wiederholt den  z.T. auch gesetzeswidrigen Rotstift ansetzt?"

+++ Sobald unsere Kritik an die √ñffentlichkeit geht, wird dann schnell alles wie √ºblich ge√§ndert.
Die MZ bekam dann auf eigentlich unsere Kritik und Fragen auch eine Antwort: Darin sind unsere Forderungen pl√∂tzlich "Selbstverst√§ndlich" und "√ºblich".
+++

+++ Die Initiative Faire Gagen und damit  unsere, weiter zunehmende Anh√§ngerschaft, wird diese Einsparversuche auch allgemein keinesfalls mitgehen und weiterhin offen und transparent f√ºr alle Filmschaffenden, den Finger in die Wunde legen. +++

Zudem fordern wir eine Gleichbehandlung der Filmschaffenden am gemeinsamen Set und dulden keine Zweiklassengesellschaft.

Filmschaffende aber auch ganz besonders Filmfans fordern wir auf, genau hinzusehen wenn es um eine verdiente Gage und einen respektvollen Umgang geht.

Auch daher unsere aktuelle Aktion:
H√§nde weg von miesen Gagen.
Siehe Faire Gagen.

+++ Und wie immer die Bitte der Unterst√ºtzung in jeglicher Form unsere wichtigen Beitr√§ge und  unserer aufwendigen und rein ehrenamtlichen Arbeit. Diese lebt nur von Eurer Hilfe, Eurem Engagment und Eurer Wachsamkeit  +++

So haben wir besonders dieses Jahr sehr viel f√ºr uns erreicht und nur so so werden wir gemeinsam auch mit unserern Agenturen respektvolle  Gagen und Zulagen behalten bzw. ausbauen, wo diese noch nicht √ºblich und selbstverst√§ndlich sind.

Role: Peter

 (Key Supporting ‚Äî Psychological Drama)

We are urgently seeking a London-based actor for a key supporting role in a tense psychological drama set inside a church.

Character Description:

‚Ä¢ Carries an undercurrent of grief, guilt, or restrained resentment

‚Ä¢ Able to shift subtly between controlled strength and quiet vulnerability

Project Details (Full Transparency):

This is an unpaid test shoot created as part of a small scale  project. We are operating on a student budget, and while we cannot reliably cover full travel expenses, we will provide a ¬£10 contribution toward London Underground travel for all participating actors.

The purpose of the shoot is to explore character dynamics, refine the scene, and identify potential cast for the paid full production.

All participants will receive high-quality cinematic footage for their showreel.

Availability:

Actors must be London-based and available at short notice.

## üåü **Job Title:** Global Film Judge (Remote) ‚Äì Persian Film Awards 2026 Jury

**#FilmJudge #Jury #FilmFestival #RemoteWork #Cinema #PersianCinema #FilmIndustry #Toronto #UK #France #Netherlands**

**The Opportunity:**

Are you a highly respected professional in the film industry with a passion for world cinema? The **Persian Film Awards (PFA)**, the only international platform celebrating cinema from Persian-speaking regions (Iran, Afghanistan, Tajikistan, and Kurdistan), invites you to join our 2026 Official Jury Panel.

This is a unique, flexible, and prestigious opportunity to contribute your expertise to a major global cultural event.

**What You Will Do:**
* **Role:** Serve as an Official Judge for the Persian Film Awards 2026 competition.
* **Focus:** Evaluate and honor the highest caliber of submitted films across features, documentaries, and shorts.
* **Time Commitment:** Fully flexible, based on your availability. You determine the number of films you wish to review.

**Key Benefits & Recognition:**

We value your expertise and offer significant professional benefits:

Global Access & Prestige: Invitation to our exclusive Red Carpet Events in major host cities: Toronto, France, the Netherlands, and the UK.

Hello! Would you like to be an extra on a student film project? This is your opportunity!

I'm looking for actors for my SFU 4th year Capstone film "Coiled Like the Wolf."

This will be a two-day shoot from **November 21 - November 22. Come either or both days!**

Monetary compensation will not be provided, but you will get free food!

Feel free to bring your friends! The more the merrier!

Email me at **mimnom@icloud.com **if you're interested!

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT FILM ‚ÄúTHE SCAM‚Äù (Expenses Paid)**

After a series of slick sales calls, a retired man is moments away from transferring his life savings to an investment ‚Äúadvisor‚Äù he‚Äôs never met. But when a sudden internet outage interrupts the transaction, the pause shatters the illusion ‚Äî forcing him to confront truth, desperation, and the human cost of manipulation.

**Peter (55 ‚Äì70)** ‚Äì male, well spoken

Chewing Gum x The Mindy Project x  Bridget Jones‚Äô Diary x New Girl x Crashing

Sick of the bleak reality of modern dating & inspired by unrealistic expectations set by the rom coms that raised her, delusional romantic Mika decides to take her love life into her own hands - and she‚Äôll do anything to orchestrate the perfect romance.

This is for the lovers and the cynics‚Äîa character-driven situational comedy that‚Äôs both a love letter and critique of the rom-coms that raised us.

-Non-Union

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew!

Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants that align with the series' message, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

üì£** CASTING CALL ‚Äî PAID OPPORTUNITY IN CAMBRIDGE**

I'm helping a Chinese production company cast performers for a short-form Douyin (TikTok China) series filming in Cambridge UK. The project is simple, natural and focuses on everyday interactions between people from different backgrounds.

We‚Äôre looking for young male and female performers who can play natural versions of themselves ‚Äî no heavy acting required.

‚ú® **What We‚Äôre Looking For**

Gender: Male & Female

Playing age: 20‚Äì30

Ethnicity: Caucasian

Language: Fluent English (any accent is fine, as long as it‚Äôs clear)

Comfortable acting naturally on camera

Able to follow simple scripts + light improvisation

Based in Cambridge preferred, but London/nearby areas welcome (travel covered)

**üé¨ Production Details**

Location: Cambridge, UK

Usage: Douyin (China‚Äôs TikTok)

Shoot Duration: Half-day or full-day depending on the episode

Schedule: Flexible / ongoing filming

Pay: ¬£30‚Äì¬£60 per hour (depending on experience)

Travel: Covered (if coming from London/nearby)

Food: Provided

Non-broadcast, social media series

üìÑ **About the Project**

A series of short, down-to-earth scenes showing everyday encounters between people from different backgrounds living in the UK. Performers will essentially play themselves ‚Äî relaxed, natural and conversational.

**üì© How to Apply**

Please send me a DM or email me at sanan282000@gmail.com

 with:

Your name

Your age

Your location

Your headshots

A showreel (if available)

or any acting experience you have (please mention what projects or training)

items.text:
# **Casting Call ‚Äî Student Film**

**Currently casting for a student final project film, shooting in January-February 2026.**

We‚Äôre currently looking for three actors for a student short film: two male (playing age 18-24) and one female (playing age 18-24).

No other physical features required, so open to all.

Please send showreel links and recent headshots to **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk** ‚Äî along with any other additional materials you want us to see.

Closing date is December 5th, as shooting begins in the new year. Must live near or be happy to travel to London among various locations, with travel and food fully covered.

## More Information

**Synopsis**

When Elias, a forlorn cinema clerk, encounters a mysterious figure who claims to know him, the pair embark on an emotional odyssey through memory and illusion. As the line between past and present fractures, and the distinction between the real and the surreal becomes ever-more blurred, Elias must confront the truths he‚Äôs long avoided ‚Äî and the self he‚Äôs tried to forget.

**Character overview: ELIAS**

Male, early 20s. Elias works in a cinema, struggling to come to terms with a recent emotional loss. He is slightly self-pitying, but becomes a serious, grounded character by the end.

**Character overview: LUCID**

Male, early 20s. Lucid is Elias‚Äô emotional foil: extroverted, while compassionate and mysterious.

**Character overview: ISOBELLA**

Female, early 20s. She is Elias‚Äô recent emotional loss. The whole story revolves around her, but she has minimal actual dialogue. She is a bit of a closed book, and could be played in a few ways.

**Shooting Dates**

Shooting dates to be confirmed, but will be between January and February 2026. Must be available within that window, but dates will be decided based on cast and crew availability within this time.

**Shooting Locations**

Various, including Kent, Buckinghamshire, and London.

**Expenses**

Travel and food will be provided, along with accommodation if necessary.

**Contact us**

To register your interest, please email **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk**. Please include any relevant information and links, such as showreels, headshots, and/or previous experience. No previous experience is required, but you must be able to showcase your abilities.

‚ú® Free Try-it VIRTUAL Voice Lessons + 40% Off Your First Month! (Black Friday Special!) ‚ú®

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm Colleen, a voice & piano teacher and mompreneur, the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We have an amazing team of supportive, talented teachers who work with students of all ages and experience levels. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, looking to build technique, or just getting started, we welcome you to join us! 

For Black Friday, we‚Äôre offering 40% off your first month of lessons (4 lessons!)Your first lesson is completely free to try before making any commitment. If you decide to continue, that free lesson will count toward your discounted month. 

We offer lessons in voice, piano, violin, viola, cello, guitar, and acting, taught virtual via Zoom! 

If you‚Äôd like to try a free lesson, you can sign up here:  [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

DM me if you have any questions!

items.text:
*Michael Chekhov Europe* invites you to its first workshop in the new year: 

**THE MOVING SPACE: Atmosphere and Playfulness on Stage **

with **David Zinder**, Tel Aviv, **Vladimir Baicher**, Moscow, **Suzana Nikoliƒá**, Zagreb, **Ulrich Meyer-Horsch**, Hamburg

**January 29 to February 1, 2026 **in Hamburg, Germany 

The space on stage is full of life, full of energy and breath. All an actor has to do is connect to this living space. 

What happens when we dive into the world of a given play and allow ourselves to be surprised by its specific dynamics, energy, language and space? 

Michael Chekhov‚Äôs concepts of ‚ÄúAtmosphere‚Äù (‚Äúthe soul of every performance‚Äù) and ‚ÄúThe Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Whole‚Äù will guide us through this exploration. 

*Movement in Space ‚Äì Objective Atmosphere ‚Äì Spatial Relationship ‚Äì Personal Atmosphere ‚Äì Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Whole ‚Äì Organic breathing ‚Äì Playfulness ‚Äì Ensemble *

items.summary:
*Michael Chekhov Europe* invites you to its first workshop in the new year: 

**THE MOVING SPACE: Atmosphere and Playfulness on Stage **

with **David Zinder**, Tel Aviv, **Vladimir Baicher**, Moscow, **Suzana Nikoliƒá**, Zagreb, **Ulrich Meyer-Horsch**, Hamburg

**January 29 to February 1, 2026 **in Hamburg, Germany 

The space on stage is full of life, full of energy and breath. All an actor has to do is connect to this living space. 

What happens when we dive into the world of a given play and allow ourselves to be surprised by its specific dynamics, energy, language and space? 

Michael Chekhov‚Äôs concepts of ‚ÄúAtmosphere‚Äù (‚Äúthe soul of every performance‚Äù) and ‚ÄúThe Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Whole‚Äù will guide us through this exploration. 

*Movement in Space ‚Äì Objective Atmosphere ‚Äì Spatial Relationship ‚Äì Personal Atmosphere ‚Äì Feeling of Ease, Form, Beauty and the Whole ‚Äì Organic breathing ‚Äì Playfulness ‚Äì Ensemble *

Michael Chekhov Europe Training ‚Äì module 2

Tuition fee: 450‚Ç¨ / 490‚Ç¨

**CASTING CALL: LIVE SHOW HOSTS**

Los Angeles (Hollywood Studio)

**Firework** is seeking energetic, camera-ready **Live Show Hosts** to lead interactive livestream product demonstrations!

**PAY:** $25-$40/hour (based on experience)

**ROLE DETAILS:**
* Host live product shows from our Hollywood, CA studio
* Present tech & lifestyle products in an authentic, conversational style
* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee
* Average 5-10 hours/week (rarely exceeds 15 hours)
* Mostly weekdays, 8 AM - 8 PM PT

**WE'RE LOOKING FOR:**
* Strong on-camera presence & natural speaking ability
* Reliable, punctual, professional
* Available weekdays during business hours
* Prior hosting/livestream/UGC/acting experience preferred but not required

**AUDITION OPTIONS:**

**Option 1: On-Site Audition**
* Dates: December 10-11, 2025
* Time: 10 AM - 1 PM PT
* 10-15 min audition (3-min one-take hosting scenario)

**Option 2: Self-Tape Submission**
* Deadline: December 11, 2025 (11:59 PM PT)
* 3 minutes, vertical, one continuous take
* Host any tech/electronic product as if live
* Email to: Kimmy@fireworkhq.com
* Subject: [Your Name] ‚Äì Live Show Host Submission - LA Digital Showroom Host - Self Tape Submission

Now casting couples in mixed orientation relationships for a new documentary series with a major cable network.

Mixed orientation relationships, often known as lavender partnerships, involve two partners who differ in their sexual orientation. We want to hear from couples who live together, share a daily life, and are engaged, married, or soon to be engaged.

This series will explore how couples navigate identity, commitment, outside expectations, and the realities of loving in a way that challenges societal norms.

If this describes you or someone you know, you can share your story at the link below.

mixedorientationcasting.castingcrane.com

VANCOUVER CREATORS ‚Äî CASTING NOW üé¨

Fourth Frame Media is making a bold new social series that explores identity, groupthink, and how we judge others. If you‚Äôre vibrant, curious, and outspoken, we want you on camera. Filming is in Vancouver, BC (local talent only).

Volunteer-based, and the winner takes home a prize.

Topics we‚Äôre shooting:

* Do I Look Like My Job?

* Best Friend Chooses Your Partner ‚Äî Person Seeking Partner

* Is the Canadian Dream Still Alive?

* Match 30 people to their jobs

* Can People Match Your Income to You?

Apply here: https://www.4thframemedia.com/casting

Please share with friends in Vancouver who‚Äôd love this!

CASTING CALL

As You Like It by William Shakespeare 
Directed by Bronwen Maeve and Hannah Scott

The Shakespeare All Year Theatre Society would love to encourage all to submit for our upcoming production of As You Like It set at a Renaissance Festival! The Bard‚Äôs enduring comedy brought to life in a Vancouver heritage building. 

Submission Deadline: Dec 7th 11:59pm

Audition dates: Jan 4th and 6th

Rehearsals: Wednesday evening and Saturday or Sunday afternoon

Show dates: April 30th - May 16th

Please Submit a Headshot and Resume to saysociety24@gmail.com
Subject line: As You Like It Submission - [FIRST AND LAST NAME]
Please include which character(s) you are submitting for, if any in mind.
Please submit for any role regardless of suggested age or gender.

We‚Äôre looking for talented female performers to join our team as the K-Pop Demon Hunters characters ‚Äì Rumi, Zoey & Mira!

You‚Äôll be bringing these high-energy, magical characters to life at children‚Äôs parties, home visits, and special events

üé§ What‚Äôs Involved:

Performing as your assigned character (costumes & wigs provided)

Singing, dancing, and interacting with children

Hosting fun party games and activities

Creating unforgettable memories for kids!

üíÉ Requirements:

Good dance level and some singing experience

Confident, fun, and great with children

Valid DBS check and experience working with kids

Available every Saturday & Sunday (with some weekday events too)

Immediate start available

üí∞ Pay Rates:

¬£200 ‚Äì 2-hour party

¬£130 ‚Äì 1-hour party

¬£60‚Äì 30-minute visit

üëó Costumes and wigs are fully provided ‚Äì just bring your talent and energy!

If you love performing, adore kids, and want to be part of something magical, apply now!

Send us a message with your name, experience, DBS status, availability, and a short performance clip (if possible).

items.text:
Hi Everyone! I run a nonprofit that provides children who have lost a parent or sibling with a special gift or experience to help them on their grief journey. In June 2026 we are hosting a 5-day free theater day-camp in Boulder for these bereaved children. We are partnering with an Atlanta-based theater company, Destination Theatre. If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

Looking for a couple (ages ~28-40) with a dog, OR a couple with one young kid (~1-6yo).

Thank you!

message.text: Am ersten Dezember 2025 eine erotische Lesung von G√∂tz van Ooyen im Lindenhof Theater in Braunschweig erleben. Karten gibt es bei der Konzertkasse und bei Musikalien Bartels und an der Abendkasse ab 18.30. die Lesung beginnt um 19.30.

AUDITION P√Ö ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù I JANUAR üèÜ
S√¶t kryds i kalenderen nu! Audition p√• Nyborg Voldspils n√¶ste store sommermusical under √•ben himmel finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026. Til forestillingen s√∏ges ca. 30 skuespillere, sangere og dansere i alle aldre fra 15 √•r og op til b√•de roller og ensemble. Selve pr√∏veforl√∏bet starter i februar 2026. Der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december 2025 p√• Nyborg Voldspils hjemmeside, hvor man allerede nu kan k√∏be billetter til forestillingen: nyborgvoldspil.dk

ANG√ÖENDE ENSEMBLE, DANS OG KOR: 
Ensemblet medvirker l√∏bende i forestillingen i mange forskellige scener/kostumer og roller/funktioner. Flere fra ensemblet har replik(ker) undervejs. √ònsker man at g√• til audition som danser uden at skulle synge eller have replikker i forestillingen, er dette ogs√• muligt. Inden for dans er ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù en af de musicals med det bredeste felt af genrer, lige fra Las Vegas- og Broadway-showdans til cancan, disco, folkedans, jazzballet, cheerleading og step samt meget mere, og derudover byder koreografierne p√• uendeligt mange komiske indslag og vinkler. Vi gl√¶der os derfor at se mange st√¶rke dansere til audition, uanset om man har erfaring eller ej inden for de individuelle genrer. G√•r man til audition inden for sang og bliver udtaget til koret blandt rollerne/ensemblet, synger man med p√• mange af de 24 numre i forestillingen ud over at indg√• i mange af de komiske indslag og scener undervejs.

ANG√ÖENDE ROLLER:
N√•r der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december, kan man l√¶se alt om de individuelle roller i forestillingen samt hvad man skal forberede, hvis man g√•r op p√• en rolle eller som ensemble. G√•r man op til ensemblet udelukkende som danser (uden at ville synge eller have replikker i forestillingen), vil man ikke skulle forberede noget hjemmefra. 

ANG√ÖENDE FORESTILLINGEN:
G√∏r dig klar til et latter-festbrag uden lige og glem alt, hvad du tror du ved om musicals ‚Äì og riddere! "SPAMALOT" er baseret p√• den komiske filmklassiker "Monty Python og de sk√∏re riddere" fra 1975 og kaster dig direkte ind i et vanvittigt middelaldereventyr fyldt med latter, kokosn√∏dder, uendelige forvirringer og totalt meningsl√∏se heltebedrifter! 
Forestillingen f√∏lger Kong Arthur og hans noget alternative Riddere af Det Runde Bord, som begiver sig ud p√• en b√•de farlig, t√•belig og fuldst√¶ndig absurd jagt efter Den Hellige Gral. Undervejs m√∏der de alt fra franske forn√¶rmelser til dansende munke, en dr√¶berkanin, dansenymfer, flyvende k√∏er ‚Äì og ikke mindst en vaske√¶gte musicaldiva med stort D!
Der er satire, sk√∏re jokes samt catchy sange og dansenumre i overflod (hvem kan ikke huske "Always Look on the Bright Side of Life"?) i et festfyrv√¶rkeri af b√•de en hyldest til og parodi af musicalgenren. Det er uforudsigeligt, ufiltreret og helt ustyrligt morsomt. En skaml√∏st vidunderlig teateroplevelse for fans af Broadway-musicals og af Monty Pythons forrygende humor ‚Äì og alle dem, der snart bliver det!
"SPAMALOT" har de seneste tyve √•r haft sin sejrsgang over hele verden og blev efter sin debut p√• Broadway i 2005 nomineret til hele 14 Tony-priser og vandt blandt andet for √Örets Bedste Musical. Det bliver med garanti en uforglemmelig og ridderligt underholdende sommer i 2026 ‚Äì for b√•de publikum og de medvirkende!
Nyborg Voldspils ops√¶tning af ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù er den f√∏rste udend√∏rsopf√∏rsel af forestillingen p√• Fyn nogensinde og instrueres af Rasmus Mansachs, der tidligere har instrueret de to ‚ÄùVi maler byen r√∏d: The Musical‚Äù-ops√¶tninger i henholdsvis 2021 og 2025. K√∏b billetter til ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù allerede nu her: nyborgvoldspil.dk

AUDITIONTILMELDING:
Der √•bnes op for tilmeldinger medio december 2025. Audition finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026. Det vil blive meldt ud p√• Nyborg Voldspils Facebook- og Instagram-profiler, s√• snart man kan tilmelde sig og l√¶se mere om de individuelle roller, ensemblet og selve pr√∏veplanen. Vi ses til auditon! 

Nyborg Voldspil pr√¶senterer:
‚ÄùMonty Python‚Äôs SPAMALOT‚Äù
16. juli ‚Äì 8. august 2026
Instrukt√∏r: Rasmus Mansachs
Sanginstrukt√∏r/korleder: Johan Berg
Koreograf: Thea Boel Gjerum

Tonight and tomorrow only at No Square Theatre in Laguna Beach!

Get your tickets at: [https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804](https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExdE9CMUlNdmlWaHQ1Z0hXRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkDzUxNDc3MTU2OTIyODA2MQABHhigjsOFZIS1vnXu10jY_YsHWJ5nXvz5lgiqWRc5_TvZ_pxZxMayZs6Vc-tX_aem_Qgp-5aGk8mHoi59iA-L5bQ)

SHE KILLS MONSTERS: YOUNG ADVENTURERS EDITION, a play by Qui Nguyen and directed by No Square Theatre Artistic Director, Joe Lauderdale, tells the story of high schooler Agnes Evans as she deals with the death of her younger sister, Tilly. When Agnes finds Tilly‚Äôs Dungeons & Dragons notebook, she gets pulled into an exciting adventure in the imaginary world that was her sister‚Äôs escape. The story is a thrilling, fast-paced dramatic comedy laden with homicidal fairies, nasty ogres, and ‚Äô90s pop culture celebrating both the geek and the warrior inside all of us.

November 22 & 23 Only!

I am in the process of getting new headshots, my casting types are Bar tender, social worker, store assistant, receptionist, or my muggle job is a mechanic so can do that as well haha. 

My castings so far have been PA and Therapist

Facebook are doing really well in taking it down super quickly in fairness to them, but I think for the now, the simplest thing is whilst this is happening is to pause the group for a short while whilst Facebook/ law enforcement get to the bottom of it to prevent the perpetrators from doing this. sharedPost.text:
Sharing on behalf of BetweenGigs Casting!!

New Hampshire Casting Call for Union & Non-Union Actors!!

Casting is NOT restricted to New England!! 

Casting for a Sci-Fi trailer.

Casting two actors for a proof-of-concept trailer for an episodic sci-fi thriller. It will be shot at the state of the art Studio Lab facility in Derry NH in mid January. This is a paid gig. Both union and non union talent may submit. A Travel/Lodging budget is available, should talent cast be from outside the New England market.

Please see the details below and submit your materials to casting@humanoriginals.com by end of day Sunday, November 23. Please include contact information for your agent or manager if you have one.

************
Project Title: Resonance: Earth 101
Project Type: Proof-of-Concept Trailer
Union: SAG-AFTRA (Micro-Budget Agreement Pending): Roles are open to both union & non union actors.
Production Company: HumanOriginals
Usage: Online, and client/investor/distributer presentations

Shoot Dates: Two days. Tentatively scheduled for January 13 & 14 2026

Shoot Location: Studio Lab, Derry NH

Fit Date/Table Read: TBD. A stipend will be available
Tech Rehearsal Dates (1-2): TBD. A stipend will be available
Travel Stipend/Lodging: TBD, depending on talent's travel distance.

Shoot/Usage Compensation: $1,000/day per talent.
Meals, credit, and copy will also be provided.

SYNOPSIS
Resonance: Earth 101 is a sci-fi thriller proof-of-concept trailer.

Shortly after crashing on Earth in 1983, Kara discovers a mysterious VHS tape in an abandoned warehouse. This triggers a recorded message from Josh, a Brooklyn teen who seems to know her story, even before they‚Äôve met. Through his nervous humor, warnings about Earth, and a mixtape he calls ‚ÄúEarth 101", Josh offers Kara both survival tools and an unexpected connection.

ROLES
JOSH
‚Ä¢ Male, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A hidden tech prodigy from 1983 Brooklyn ‚Äî sharp, curious, and socially awkward, hiding brilliance behind sarcasm. Nervous yet magnetic. He risks everything to help Kara find her way on Earth.

KARA
‚Ä¢ Female, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A resilient and observant young woman carrying a maturity beyond her years. Athletic and graceful, Kara looks both innocent and ancient, as though she‚Äôs already written into myth. Her arrival on Earth sets off an unexpected chain of events.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS
To be considered for an audition, please email headshot (or current photo), resume, and reel (if available) to casting@humanoriginals.com.

Subject Line of your email should read: Role name / Your name

Submissions are requested by 5:00pm Sunday, November 23. 

If selected to audition, instructions & script for a self-taped audition will be sent to you.

Callbacks, if needed, will be via Zoom.

Peaccceee!! If you've been wondering what I've been up to... I invite you to attend an event this Sunday, Nov 30th at 3pm. It's been a while since I've organized an event, but I've partnered with Flink to host a low-key, yet vibrant gathering for brand ambassadors, influencers, content creators, actors, actresses, and film industry professionals.

Please note that attendance is limited to those in Houston or traveling, and RSVP registration is required. Feel free to bring a friend/associate.
